==Rationale==

Version bits provide several advantages over previous deployment methods:

# '''Parallel Deployments''': Up to 29 soft forks can be signaled simultaneously
# '''Clear Thresholds''': Miners explicitly signal readiness
# '''Timeout Safety''': Failed deployments automatically expire
# '''Miner Coordination''': Reduces risk of chain splits

The 90% threshold ensures strong consensus before activation.

==Backwards Compatibility==

Version bits are backwards compatible. Nodes that do not understand a deployment will:
* Accept blocks regardless of version bits
* Continue normal operation after activation

Old nodes may not enforce new rules after activation, potentially following an invalid chain.

